&lt;td&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This project aimed to solve the spatial variability of snow depth
problem in the Earth system modeling. A snow model for representing sub-grid
variability of snow depth was coupled into the Rapid Update Cycle Land
Surface Model (RUC LSM), and its impacts on the LSM was evaluated.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
